    "body": "Hello everyone,\n\nI tried to understand your discussion but not sure if it is answering my issue. I got the same error: \"curl: (52) Empty reply from server\", but ONLY when the node is running in a container (maybe a docker only issue...?).\n\nMy commands:\n\n```\ndocker run -d --name=eth -v $PWD:/data -p 8545:8545 -p 30303:30303 ethereum/client-go --networkid 12011 --genesis /data/mygenesis.json --datadir  /data/data_node1 --nodiscover --rpc --rpcport 8545 --rpccorsdomain '\"*\"'\n\ncurl -X POST --data '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_accounts\",\"params\":[],\"id\":1}' localhost:8545\ncurl: (52) Empty reply from server\n\ndocker exec eth curl -X POST --data '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_accounts\",\"params\":[],\"id\":1}' localhost:8545\n{\"id\":1,\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"result\":[\"0x8dae714e9227258a1d5a15352a69ed3243a25e09\",\"0xeb41741fdba96fe200a0427237893c97f887cdb5\"]}\n```\n\nI can query from inside the container, but not from outside (port are indeed mapped -p 8545:8545).\nAny help will be great!\n\nThanks a lot!\nAnd very good week! ;-)\nGreg.\n",
